                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A 4e/16: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-07T16:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 7, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 7—8:39 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. I propose Chinese proposal that Shanghai market values for six months, October
                    to April, be taken as the basis new tariff. Arnold.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
